name: No Bake Strawberry Cheesecake
author: mamasguardianangel
summary: Light and fluffy no bake cheesecake with a strawberry surprise taste.
ingredients: 1 (3 ounce) package strawberry-flavored gelatin (such as Jell-O®)
directions: Dissolve strawberry gelatin in boiling water in a bowl; cool in refrigerator until thick, but not set, about 20 minutes
Beat cream cheese, sugar, and vanilla extract together in a bowl until smooth
Beat evaporated milk in a separate bowl with an electric mixer until whipped and thick
Gradually pour strawberry gelatin mixture into evaporated milk, beating constantly
Fold cream cheese mixture into gelatin-milk mixture to form cheesecake filling
Set graham cracker crust on a baking sheet or plate to maintain stability
Refrigerate until cake is set, at least 3 1/2 hours
